The patched amtlib.dll works on Photoshop CS5 32-bit. However, it does not work on the 64-bit version. App crashes immediately on launch.

I got the Photoshop 0xc00007 crash on load error when I used the 32-bit included DLL in the 64-bit directories.  It is not necessary.

Confirmed working on Windows 7 x64 Professional WITH x64 Photoshop using ORIGINAL 64 bit amtlib.dll file.  In other words I did NOT have to replace the amtlib.dll after install in the 64-bit directories for PS and Premiere although I did replace most of the 32 bit ones.

If the 64bit versions don't work for you with the original DLL, I may have overlooked something I did.  I did restart after replacing/install and I did make sure that my internet was off when I started most programs for the first time.  Hopefully someone can confirm more systematically what causes the 64bit issues.  But it DOES work.   the only problem I see is Encore loads with an runtime error r6034 but it still loads and appears to work.  Also, this was WITHOUT uninstalling previous CS4 Master Edition.
